  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pastitsio is Greece's answer to lasagne: pasta, a spiced meat sauce, and a thick "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "béchamel",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "bechamel"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " topping baked until set and golden. The cinnamon in the meat sauce is the defining flavour, warm and sweet against the savoury lamb. This is a dish that serves a crowd and keeps well."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Use penne or rigatoni here; you want tubes that can stand upright in the dish if possible for the classic pastitsio look when sliced. Cook the pasta two minutes short of done; it finishes in the oven."
          }
        ]
      },
