      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cook the pasta"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cook {{pasta-dried}} of pasta in a large pot of well-salted boiling water for 2 minutes less than the packet says. It should be just slightly underdone. Drain, toss with a beaten egg and {{parmesan}} of grated parmesan, and set aside."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make the meat sauce"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Heat {{olive-oil}} in a large pan over medium heat. Cook {{onion}} finely chopped onions until soft, about 8 minutes. Add {{garlic}} of garlic and cook for 1 minute."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Increase the heat to medium-high and brown {{lamb-mince}} of lamb mince well, breaking up any lumps, about 8 minutes. Pour in {{red-wine}} of red wine and let it reduce by half."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add the tinned tomatoes, {{tomato-puree}} of tomato purée, the cinnamon stick, and {{allspice}} of ground allspice. Season with salt and pepper. Simmer gently for 25 minutes until the sauce is thick. Remove the cinnamon stick."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make the béchamel"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Melt {{unsalted-butter}} of butter in a medium saucepan. Stir in {{plain-flour}} of flour and cook for 2 minutes. Whisk in the warm milk gradually until you have a thick, smooth sauce. Season with salt, {{nutmeg}} of grated nutmeg, and pepper. Cool for 5 minutes, then whisk in the beaten eggs and {{parmesan}} of grated parmesan."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Assemble and bake"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C. Grease a large rectangular baking tin. Spread half the pasta in an even layer on the base. Spoon all of the meat sauce over the pasta. Cover with the remaining pasta."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Pour the béchamel over the top and smooth it with a spatula. Bake for 45 minutes until the top is deep golden and the filling is bubbling at the edges. Rest for 15 minutes before slicing."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "symptom": "The pasta is soft and the layers don't hold together when sliced",
              "cause": "Pasta was overcooked before baking",
              "fix": "Undercook the pasta by at least 2 minutes. It absorbs moisture from the sauce during baking and will reach the right texture in the oven."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "The meat sauce tastes flat",
              "cause": "Cinnamon stick didn't have time to infuse, or sauce not reduced enough",
              "fix": "Simmer the sauce for the full 25 minutes. The cinnamon flavour develops with time. Add a small pinch of allspice if it still tastes thin."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "The béchamel doesn't set firm",
              "cause": "Too much milk, or eggs not added, or not baked long enough",
              "fix": "The sauce needs to be quite thick before the eggs go in. Check the baking time: the top should be a deep golden colour and the filling should not wobble when shaken."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "The dish is watery",
              "cause": "Meat sauce too thin",
              "fix": "Simmer the sauce until it holds its shape when spooned onto a plate. If it pools, cook it for another 10 minutes uncovered."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Where this dish lives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pastitsio sits alongside moussaka as one of the great Greek oven bakes. It appears on every family table at celebrations and is the dish many Greeks describe as the first thing they want when they come home. Like lasagne in Italy, it varies slightly from household to household; some families add a little ground clove, some use all beef, some layer the pasta all in one go. The cinnamon and the thick béchamel are the constants."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
